    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="327"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1648.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Russell</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 14.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 22, of the
                    8th instant, in which you report that the financial situation in the Dominican
                    Republic is still in a hopeless state.</p>
                <p>The Department approves your action in advising the deputy receiver general of
                    Dominican customs against making the advances mentioned in paragraph two of your
                    despatch.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
